      data:
        difficulty: 0
        question:
        - This is the property that objects need to transfer in order to perform
          work. Which of the following best describes this?
        - This is the trait that objects must convey in order to do work. Which of
          the following best describes this?
        - This is the characteristic that things must possess in order to do labor.
          Which of the following best describes this?
        correctAnswer:
        - Energy
        wrongAnswers:
        - Kinetic Energy
        - Conservative Force
        - Potential Energy
        choiceCount: 4
    - rid: 7832858373401083968
      type: {class: MultipleChoiceItem, ns: ProjectATLAS.Quiz, asm: Assembly-CSharp}
      data:
        difficulty: 0
        question:
        - This energy only transfers and changes form, from one body to another.
          Which of the following best describes this?
        correctAnswer:
        - Law of Conservation of Energy
        wrongAnswers:
        - Spring Force
        - Friction Energy
        - Kinetic Energy
        choiceCount: 4
    - rid: 7832858373401083969
      type: {class: MultipleChoiceItem, ns: ProjectATLAS.Quiz, asm: Assembly-CSharp}
      data:
        difficulty: 0
        question:
        - This energy is stored by an object when it is pulled apart or compressed.
          Which of the following best describes this?
        - This is the energy held by an object when it is pushed apart or compacted.
          Which of the following best describes this?
        - This is the energy retained by an object as it is pushed apart or compressed.
          Which of the following best describes this?
        correctAnswer:
        - Elestic Potential Energy
        wrongAnswers:
        - Spring Energy
        - Energy
        - Gravitational Energy
        choiceCount: 4
    - rid: 7832858373401083970
